    <section>
      <h2>The Problem ðŸŽ¯</h2>
      <p>
        Healthcare providers face high volumes of patient inquiries and long wait times for initial assessment.  
        The business need was an automated, medically accurate triage system to reduce staff load and improve patient experience.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>My Role ðŸ’¡</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Lead AI Engineer & Architect â€“ end-to-end owner.</li>
        <li>Designed system architecture, selected LLMs, integrated medical ontologies.</li>
        <li>Designed scalable cloud deployment (GKE + Cloud Run).</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The Solution ðŸš€</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Clinical Reasoning:</strong> Gemini 1.5 Pro + Med-PaLM 2 with Chain-of-Thought prompting.</li>
        <li><strong>Knowledge Layer:</strong> SNOMED-CT & ICD-10 entity linking via Google Healthcare NL.</li>
        <li><strong>Conversation Flow:</strong> Vertex AI Agent Builder + Dialogflow CX for stateful dialogue.</li>
        <li><strong>Deployment:</strong> Containerized on GKE (stateful) & Cloud Run (stateless).</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Results & Impact ðŸ“ˆ</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>40 %</strong> reduction in average triage time.</li>
        <li><strong>95 %</strong> accuracy vs. historical nurse triage.</li>
        <li><strong>1 000+</strong> concurrent sessions validated in stress tests.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

